        "body": "Promote GitHub save into the main toolbar Save workflow. On first save, let the user choose a destination such as a connected private repo or connected public repo. After that, Save should commit directly to the remembered destination, while Save As and destination editing expose repo, branch, and path details when needed.",
        "status": "todo",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "critical",
        "estimateHours": "10",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "Toolbar Save commits directly when a graph already has a GitHub destination",
          "First save can choose a connected destination without forcing the full panel workflow",
          "Save As or destination editing exposes repo, branch, and path when needed",
          "Recent or default public/private destinations can be reused"
        ],
