    {
      "id": "github-app-plan",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Implementation Plan",
      "position": {
        "x": -260,
        "y": 1040
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1 — Session + Server Boundary\n- define session shape\n- add auth routes\n- establish GitHub login + callback\n\n## Phase 2 — Installation + Repo Access\n- list installations\n- select active installation\n- support repo picker and manual owner/repo entry\n\n## Phase 3 — Replace Client PAT Flows\n- route commit/load/delete through server\n- remove PAT UI and PAT storage\n- keep public reads working\n\n## Phase 4 — Save Target Model\n- treat repo/path as a remembered destination\n- make toolbar Save commit directly when destination exists\n- keep Save As / destination editing for advanced cases\n\n## Phase 5 — github:// Resolution\n- keep github:// as a locator\n- use public direct reads where allowed\n- use server-backed reads when auth is required\n\n## Phase 6 — Cutover\n- remove PAT code paths\n- update docs\n- verify write flows only use app-backed auth",
        "memo": "",
        "link": "",
        "html": "",
        "svg": "",
